     <h1 align="center">Dr. Edee Schulze, <br> Vice president for student life/dean of students </h1> 
     <p><img src="images/EdeeSchulze_000.jpg" width="150" height="225" alt="Edee Schulze">Dear Parents, </p> 
     <p>I am in my first months at Westmont, having arrived here in July 2014 after twenty-seven years at two other Christian higher education institutions. It hasn’t taken me long to realize just how exceptional Westmont is, and I’m not just referring to the beautiful weather and the unparalleled scenery. It is a privilege to be at a place so focused in a commitment to provide a top-rate Christian, liberal arts, residential, global, undergraduate education. That is a tall order! </p> 
     <p class="txt_dont_wrap">In Student Life at Westmont, we partner with faculty to accomplish the educational mission of the institution, seizing every opportunity available to us to support and challenge students in their growth and to provide learning opportunities that work hand-in-hand with what they are experiencing in the classroom. We count it a privilege to stand at the crossroads with students on their journey, whatever their need or ambition, helping to shape them as leaders, scholars and servants of Christ. </p> 
     <p>I suspect you chose Westmont from the myriad of options in higher education because you recognize the impact this kind of community and experience will have on your son or daughter. We are grateful for the chance to know and work with your student and to be part of his or her development here on campus and around the world in Westmont’s various off-campus programs. One mom of a Westmont student told me how significant it was to her and her family that her son was chosen by Westmont. It was a vote of confidence to him that he could thrive and rise to the challenge of a rigorous Christ-centered education. Students are admitted because we believe they will succeed in meeting the goals this opportunity and experience places before them. We also choose students because we believe they will make contributions to this community that will mark us, make us better and contribute to our shared purpose. It’s a privilege to be chosen and we are grateful that you are joining us in this endeavor!</p> 
     <p>On the threshold of the year, whether you are a new or a veteran Westmont parent, we are all facing another opportunity to trust God and release our students to His care and guidance in their educational pursuits. We pray for our students regularly and as you go through this year, releasing them into the loving hands of God our Father and trusting that His work in their lives will reign supreme, we will pray for you as well.<br> </p> 
     <p> This website provides important information for you as a parent of a Westmont student. If you have questions or concerns, we hope you will contact us. </p> 
     <p>May the full blessings of God be yours and ours this coming year,</p> 
     <p>Edee Schulze, Ph.D. </p> 
     <p> Vice President for Student Life and Dean of Students <br> Westmont College<br> <a href="tel:%28805%29%20565-7421">805-565-6028<br> </a></p> 
     <!-- InstanceEndEditable --> 
